Preheat your #oven{} to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7. Boil a full #kettle{}.

Heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a large, wide-bottomed #ovenproof pan{} on medium heat.

> TIP: If you don't have an ovenproof pan, use a normal pan and transfer to an ovenproof dish before baking.

Once hot, add the @British Smoked Bacon Lardons{90%g}. Fry, stirring occasionally,
until golden, ~{4-5%mins}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw meat. Cook bacon thoroughly.

Meanwhile, peel and grate the @Garlic Clove{2}(peeled and grated) (or use a #garlic press{}).

Once the bacon has cooked, add the garlic to the pan and cook for ~{30%secs}.

Add the @Risotto Rice{175%g} to the bacon. Stir and cook until the edges of the rice
are translucent, ~{1-2%mins}.

Stir in the @Chicken Stock Paste{15%g} and @Boiled Water{500%ml}. Season with @salt{} and
@pepper{}.

Bring back up to the boil, then pop a lid on the pan (or cover with #foil{}) and bake
on the middle shelf of your oven until the rice is cooked and the water has been
absorbed, ~{20-25%mins}.

When the risotto is cooked, remove it from the oven, then stir in the @Peas{120%g}
and @Baby Spinach{40%g} until piping hot and wilted, ~{1-2%mins}.

Mix the @Fresh Pesto{32%g}, @Grated Hard Italian Style Cheese{20%g} and
@Butter{20%g} into the risotto until melted and well combined.

Taste and season with salt and pepper if needed.

> TIP: Add a splash of water to loosen the risotto if needed.

Share the bacon and pea risotto between your #bowls{}.

Drizzle over the @Balsamic Glaze{12%ml} to finish.

Enjoy!